@node Top
@top VibeOS Manual

VibeOS is an amd64 monolithic kernel prototype that boots through Multiboot2,
switches itself into long mode, mounts a read-only initramfs root and a
read-only ext2 @file{/usr} image, and runs a Linux-ABI userspace built mostly
from static musl binaries.

The repository has two standing policy constraints that shape almost every part
of the system:

@itemize @bullet
@item The dynamic loader path exists, but it is still considered buggy in
practice.  Static linking is preferred unless it is impossible.
@item Musl is preferred over glibc when possible, and the build wrappers use
@code{zig cc} or @code{zig c++} with @code{x86_64-linux-musl} targets for most
userspace packages.
@end itemize

This manual is written in GNU Texinfo style and is split into many source files
so that the overall system reference can grow without collapsing into a single
monolithic document.

